<item>
            <title>[LU-13797] quiet e2fsck &quot;extent tree (at level 1) could be narrower&quot; message</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13797</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The e2fsck error &quot;&lt;tt&gt;Inode 4457806 extent tree (at level 1) could be narrower. Optimize&amp;lt;y&amp;gt;?&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; can be very noisy (many thousands of lines), and doesn&apos;t really improve filesystem performance in any significant way (typically saving a few extent index blocks for files that were written with holes that were later filled in).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better to change the e2fsck default to &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; optimize the extents, to avoid confusing users with a lot of messages and giving them worries that their filesystem is corrupted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve discussed this with Ted already, and he agrees that this is an acceptable change. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
